int dataType

String typeName

int columnSize
        column size.

      • bufferLength

        @ColumnLabel(value="BUFFER_LENGTH")
@NotUsed
int bufferLength
        is not used.

      • decimalDigits

        @ColumnLabel(value="DECIMAL_DIGITS")
Integer decimalDigits
        the number of fractional digits. Null is returned for data types where DECIMAL_DIGITS is not applicable.

      • numPrecRadix

        @ColumnLabel(value="NUM_PREC_RADIX")
int numPrecRadix
        Radix (typically either 10 or 2).

      • nullable

        @ColumnLabel(value="NULLABLE")
int nullable
        is NULL allowed.
        • DatabaseMetaData.columnNoNulls - might not allow NULL values
        • DatabaseMetaData.columnNullable - definitely allows NULL values
        • DatabaseMetaData.columnNullableUnknown - nullability unknown

      • remarks

        @ColumnLabel(value="REMARKS")
@NillableBySpecification
String remarks
        comment describing column (may be null)

      • columnDef

        @ColumnLabel(value="COLUMN_DEF")
@NillableBySpecification
String columnDef
        default value for the column, which should be interpreted as a string when the value is enclosed in single quotes (may be null)

int sqlDataType

int charOctetLength

      • ordinalPosition

        @ColumnLabel(value="ORDINAL_POSITION")
int ordinalPosition
        index of column in table (starting at 1).

      • isNullable

        @ColumnLabel(value="IS_NULLABLE")
String isNullable
        ISO rules are used to determine the nullability for a column.
        • YES --- if the column can include NULLs
        • NO --- if the column cannot include NULLs
        • empty string --- if the nullability for the column is unknown

      • scopeCatalog

        @ColumnLabel(value="SCOPE_CATALOG")
@NillableBySpecification
String scopeCatalog
        catalog of table that is the scope of a reference attribute (null if DATA_TYPE isn't REF).

      • scopeSchema

        @ColumnLabel(value="SCOPE_SCHEMA")
@NillableBySpecification
String scopeSchema
        schema of table that is the scope of a reference attribute (null if the DATA_TYPE isn't REF).

      • scopeTable

        @ColumnLabel(value="SCOPE_TABLE")
@NillableBySpecification
String scopeTable
        table name that this the scope of a reference attribute (null if the DATA_TYPE isn't REF).

      • sourceDataType

        @ColumnLabel(value="SOURCE_DATA_TYPE")
@NillableBySpecification
String sourceDataType
        source type of a distinct type or user-generated Ref type, SQL type from Types (null if dataType isn't Types.DISTINCT or user-generated Types.REF)

      • isAutoincrement

        @ColumnLabel(value="IS_AUTOINCREMENT")
String isAutoincrement
        Indicates whether this column is auto incremented.
        • YES --- if the column is auto incremented
        • NO --- if the column is not auto incremented
        • empty string --- if it cannot be determined whether the column is auto incremented

      • isGeneratedcolumn

        @ColumnLabel(value="IS_GENERATEDCOLUMN")
@SuppressionPath(value="column/isGeneratedcolumn")
String isGeneratedcolumn
        Indicates whether this is a generated column.
    • YES --- if this a generated column
    • NO --- if this not a generated column
    • empty string --- if it cannot be determined whether this is a generated column
